CATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> should not recognize the Palestinian state the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> declared in November. The rest were split between support for recognition and no opinion. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> has said that it will not negotiate with the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> because the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>'s charter calls for <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s destruction, but that it would negotiate with other representatives of the Palestinians. Other Arab nations, however, have declared the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> the only legitimate representative of the Palestinians. In the survey, 63 percent said some group other than the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> could represent the <LOCATION> Palestinians </LOCATION> in negotiations with <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>. And nearly seven respondents in 10 said the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> should not try to force <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> to negotiate with the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> by threatening sanctions. The survey had a three-point margin of sampling error. <ORGANIZATION> Media </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a communications company based in <LOCATION> Richmond </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Va. </LOCATION>, publishes the Richmond Times-Dispatch, the Richmond News Leader, the <LOCATION> Tampa </LOCATION> -LRB- <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION> -RRB- <ORGANIZATION> Tribune </ORGANIZATION> and the <LOCATION> Winston-Salem </LOCATION> -LRB- <LOCATION> N.C. </LOCATION> -RRB- Journal, and operates TV stations <ORGANIZATION> WXFL </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Tampa </LOCATION>, WCBD in <LOCATION> Charleston </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> S.C. </LOCATION>, and <ORGANIZATION> WJKS </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Jacksonville </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla </LOCATION>.
