RSON>, <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> G. </PERSON> <PERSON> Neumann </PERSON> and <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Horning </PERSON>, along with <PERSON> Diana </PERSON> <PERSON> Gordon </PERSON>, a professor of political science at <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> College </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, and <PERSON> Janlori </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldman </PERSON>, an attorney with the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Civil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberties </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Union </ORGANIZATION>'s privacy and technology project.
