 Want your parking ticket fixed? Need a job reference? Having marital problems? Social Security check too low? Your son wants out of the Army? A lot of <LOCATION> Louisiana </LOCATION> residents seem to figure their representative in <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> was elected to deal with any problem for them, no matter how great or how small. Rep. <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> McCrery </PERSON> was called on by a constituent to deliver a plum to then-President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON>. He and his staff also found time to negotiate a telephone bill revision for an elderly couple who said emphatically that they had not dialed 976-LOVE, a sexy call-in line, a dozen times. Then there was the time Rep. <PERSON> Billy </PERSON> <PERSON> Tauzin </PERSON> got a call from a woman in <LOCATION> Chackbay </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> La. </LOCATION>, his hometown. `` She said she had a terrible problem,'' he said. `` I guess I was feeling real good about being a congressman, and I told her ` If you got a problem, I'll solve it.' `` So she said, ` The garbage man has n't been coming and the dogs are getting into my garbage and it's a mess.' I asked her, ` Did you call the sanitation department?' `` She waited about three seconds and said, ` <PERSON> Billy </PERSON>, I did n't know I needed to go that high.'''
